{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17599591","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17599591"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T11:57:12+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T11:57:12+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15583"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15583","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15583"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.24,0.1,0.17,0.48,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8274"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70195"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8274","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8274"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15583"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"55659"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"6774"},{"type":"tags","id":"7005"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19983"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19987"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70195","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/70195"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe thyroid gland is a vital endocrine organ located in the anterior neck region.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following correctly describes the anatomical location of the thyroid isthmus?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Anterior to the cricoid cartilage","Posterior to the second to fourth tracheal rings","Between the hyoid bone and thyroid cartilage","Anterior to the second to fourth tracheal rings","Lateral to the thyroid cartilage"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis thin band of thyroid tissue connects the right and left thyroid lobes and is \u003Cstrong\u003Eanterior to the second to fourth tracheal rings\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe isthmus is not located \u003Cstrong\u003Eanterior to the cricoid cartilage\u003C/strong\u003E or \u003Cstrong\u003Ebetween the hyoid bone and thyroid cartilage \u003C/strong\u003Eas these are too superior. It is located between the thyroid cartilage and sternal notch. The isthmus cannot be \u003Cstrong\u003Eposterior to the second to fourth tracheal rings\u003C/strong\u003E as this would place it in the oesophagus. The isthmus is a midline structure hence is not \u003Cstrong\u003Elateral to the thyroid cartilage\u003C/strong\u003E.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The thyroid isthmus connects the two thyroid lobes anterior to the 2nd-4th tracheal rings.","The thyroid isthmus is an important anatomical landmark during clinical examination and surgical procedures of the neck."],"references":["Melmed, S., Polonsky, K. S., Larsen, P. R., \u0026 Kronenberg, H. M. (2015). Williams textbook of endocrinology E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Clark, O. H., Duh, Q. Y., Kebebew, E., Gosnell, J. E., \u0026 Shen, W. T. (Eds.). (2016). Textbook of endocrine surgery. JP Medical Ltd","Young, W. F. (2011). Netter\u0027s Endocrine System: Netter Collection of Medical Illustrations: Endocrine System E-book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Wass, J. A., \u0026 Stewart, P. M. (Eds.). (2011). Oxford textbook of endocrinology and diabetes. Oxford University Press, USA."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"55659"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15583"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"55659","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions